@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place A2Zee where you want
on your computer (hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc.). No
other files or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  When first run, A2Zee displays the main menu where a row of
letters from A to Z are displayed. The two letters that are
'pressed down', and those that are between them, are the ones
used for the game. By clicking on one of the letters, you can
choose how many letters you want to play with, the minimum number
of letters playable is 8 (A to H), but you can play with all the
letters (A to Z) if you want.

  When you are ready to play the game, just click on the 'Play!'
button. This will display the game board showing the letters you
have selected.

  When playing, click on a tile containing a letter you want to
move and click on the tile where you want to place that letter.
At that moment, the two letters will switch their positions. Note
that you cannot choose the letters that are located at either ends
of the series of letters...

  To complicate matters a little, each time you move some letters,
the letters located on either side of the letters to be moved will
also change their position, as shown in the following example:

  C G A D E H B F
    ^         ^
    letters to be moved

The result:

  A B C D E F G H
    ^         ^
    moved letters

  Try to put all the letters in the correct order, in the least
amount of moves.

NOTE: when playing a game, you can go back to the main menu by
      clicking on the window's close button (or by pressing on the
      'Esc' key). If in the menu, the same action [close button or
      'Esc' key] will quit the game.

  Have fun!

